{"metadata":{"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"Components"}],"roleHeading":"Structure","externalID":"s:14OUDSComponents15OUDSRadioPickerV","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSRadioPicker","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"OUDSRadioPicker","symbolKind":"struct","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OUDSRadioPicker","kind":"identifier"}]},"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Initializers","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSRadioPicker\/init(selection:radios:placement:isOutlined:isReversed:isError:isReadOnly:hasDivider:itemsSpacing:)"],"title":"Initializers"},{"anchor":"Instance-Properties","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSRadioPicker\/body"],"title":"Instance Properties"},{"anchor":"Default-Implementations","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSRadioPicker\/View-Implementations","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSRadioPicker\/View-Implementations"],"title":"Default Implementations"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@","kind":"attribute"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSRadioPicker","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"Tag","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":"> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"where","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Tag","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SH","text":"Hashable","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Controls"]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Accessibility considerations","level":2,"anchor":"Accessibility-considerations","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Voice Over"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" will use several elements to describe the component: if component disabled \/ read only, if error context, the label and helper texts and a custom radio trait.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The picker itself does no have any defined accessiiblity value, label or identifier ; it remains in the users hands to define which one will be used.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"However if defined in the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSRadioPickerData"},{"text":" the items inside the picker will have such accessibility identifiers.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Forbidden by design","level":2,"anchor":"Forbidden-by-design","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The design system does not allow to have ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSRadioItem"},{"text":" in both an error situation and a read only state.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The design system does not allow to have ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSRadioItem"},{"text":" in both an error situation and a disabled state.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The design system does not allow to have ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSRadioItem"},{"text":" in both a read only and a disabled state.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Code samples","level":2,"anchor":"Code-samples","type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ Define the elements to display in radio buttons using OUDSRadioPickerData.","    \/\/ This object has the same properties as the OUDSRadioItem,","    \/\/ and some of them are optional withdefault values set","    var someDataToPopulate: [OUDSRadioPickerData<String>] {","        [","            OUDSRadioPickerData<String>(tag: \"Choice_1\",","                                        label: \"Virgin Holy Lava\",","                                        additionalLabel: \"Very spicy\",","                                        helper: \"No alcohol, only tasty flavors\",","                                        icon: Image(systemName: \"flame\")),","","            OUDSRadioPickerData<String>(tag: \"Choice_2\",","                                        label: \"IPA beer\",","                                        helper: \"From Brewdog company\",","                                        icon: Image(systemName: \"dog.fill\")),","","            OUDSRadioPickerData<String>(tag: \"Choice_3\",","                                        label: \"Mineral water\",","                                        icon: Image(systemName: \"waterbottle.fill\")),","        ]","    }","","    \/\/ Prepare the selection, with a value previously selected","    \/\/ Use the data and the binding for the picker.","    @State var selection: String = \"Choice_1\"","","    \/\/ Here the picker is vertical","    OUDSRadioPicker(selection: $selection, radios: someDataToPopulate)","","    \/\/ The picker can apply some settings to all its radio buttons.","    \/\/ It can be also horitzontal with a scroll indicator.","    \/\/ Here all the the radio buttons are in read only mode and use reversed layout.","    OUDSRadioPicker(selection: $selection,","                    radios: someDataToPopulate,","                    isReversed: true,","                    isReadOnly: true,","                    placement: .horitzontal(true))"],"type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Design documentation","level":2,"anchor":"Design-documentation","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There is no online specification as this component is not an official OUDSThemesContract one"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Theme rendering","level":2,"anchor":"Theme-rendering","type":"heading"},{"text":"Orange","level":3,"anchor":"Orange","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_radioPicker_Orange"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Orange Business Tools","level":3,"anchor":"Orange-Business-Tools","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_radioPicker_OrangeBusinessTools","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Sosh","level":3,"anchor":"Sosh","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_radioPicker_Sosh","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Wireframe","level":3,"anchor":"Wireframe","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_radioPicker_Wireframe"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Since","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0.14.0"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside"}]}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A picker allowing to expose several radio buttons and choose only one within the others."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Each radio button contains a “tag”, i.e. a supposed to be unique value."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The picker will expose the choosen value through this “tag”."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It has also some configuration elements which will override the one applied to nested "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSRadioItem","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" (divider, read only and error mode, layout and outlined)"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudsradiopicker"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"relationships